{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For N queries, let n i be the attempts for query i (failures capped at N m), then ANA = 1 N N i=1 n i.",
    "One attempt corresponds to a method-specific step: e.g., a search cycle for GS-MCTS, a gradient update for GCG (Zou et al., 2023), or a prompt revision for PAIR (Chao et al., 2023).",
    "Furthermore, we employ additional metrics to evaluate broader defense performance beyond ASR: (1) Robustness measures defense ability against strong or unseen attacks.",
    "(2) Over-Refusal (Cui et al., 2024) measures rate of excessive refusal on benign queries.",
    "(3) Helpfulness evaluates whether the model can provide useful suggestions even when refusing the queries."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "One attempt corresponds to a method-specific step: e.g., a search cycle for GS-MCTS, a gradient update for GCG (Zou et al., 2023), or a prompt revision for PAIR (Chao et al., 2023).",
